sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (internal)
    participant PyPI as pypi.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Pipeline as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Runtime as Runtime Pod<br/>(Elyra execution)

    rect rgb(200, 220, 240)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench via Browser
        User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/<br/>HTTPS/443
        Router->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443
        OAuth->>OAuthServer: Validate token / OAuth redirect<br/>HTTPS/6443
        OAuthServer-->>OAuth: OAuth token response<br/>JWT token
        OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward authenticated request<br/>HTTP/8888 (no auth)
        Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI response<br/>HTTP/8888
        OAuth-->>Router: Response with session cookie<br/>HTTPS/8443
        Router-->>User: JupyterLab interface<br/>HTTPS/443
    end

    rect rgb(220, 240, 200)
        Note over Jupyter,PyPI: Flow 2: Install Python Package from Workbench
        Jupyter->>PyPI: pip install {package}<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package artifacts (.whl)<br/>HTTPS/443
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install to workbench filesystem<br/>UID 1001 permissions
    end

    rect rgb(240, 220, 200)
        Note over Jupyter,Runtime: Flow 3: Run Elyra Pipeline Node (Runtime Image)
        Jupyter->>Pipeline: Submit pipeline definition<br/>HTTP/8888 Bearer Token
        Pipeline->>K8sAPI: Create pod with runtime image<br/>HTTPS/6443 Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Runtime: Pod created
        Runtime->>S3: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM credentials
        S3-->>Runtime: Model data
        Runtime->>Runtime: Execute pipeline node
        Runtime-->>Pipeline: Results
        Pipeline-->>Jupyter: Pipeline status
    end

    rect rgb(240, 200, 220)
        Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 4: kubectl/oc Commands from Workbench
        User->>Jupyter: Run "oc get pods" in terminal<br/>WebSocket
        Jupyter->>K8sAPI: API request<br/>HTTPS/6443 Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: Pod list
        Jupyter-->>User: Terminal output<br/>WebSocket
    end
